gory:Graduates of the Royal Military College, Sandhurst]]\n[[Category:Grand Commanders of the Order of Honour (Greece)]]\n[[Category:Recipients of the War Cross (Greece)]]\n[[Category:Recipients of the Military Cross]]\n[[Category:First Lords of the Admiralty]]\n[[Category:Lords Privy Seal]]\n[[Category:Members of the Privy Council of the United Kingdom]]\n[[Category:People educated at St Peter's Court]]\n[[Category:People educated at Winchester College]]\n[[Category:People associated with King's College London]]\n[[Category:Chancellors of the University of Southampton]]\n[[Category:People from Ventnor]]\n[[Category:People from Wiltshire]]\n[[Category:Presidents of the Royal Geographical Society]]\n[[Category:Special Air Service officers]]\n[[Category:Special Boat Service officers]]\n[[Category:Crete in World War II]]\n[[Category:Leaders of the House of Lords]]\n[[Category:British Army Commandos officers]]\n[[Category:Fellows of the Royal Geographical Society]]\n[[Category:Cayzer family]]\n[[Category:Schroders people]]\n[[Category:Fellows of the Royal Scottish Geographical Society]]\n", "name_user": "Gaia Octavia Agrippa", "label": "safe", "comment": "\u2192\u200etop:cl", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/George_Jellicoe,_2nd_Earl_Jellicoe"}
{"title_page": "2002\u201303 FIS Cross-Country World Cup", "text_new": "{{Use dmy dates|date=May 2012}}\n{{Infobox Double Wintersport World Cup\n| title=<!--[[File:F\u00e9d\u00e9ration internationale de ski (logo).svg|28px]]--> 2002\u201303 FIS Cross-Country World Cup\n| competition1= Overall\n| competition1men= {{flagicon|SWE}} [[Mathias Fredriksson]]\n| competition1ladies= {{flagicon|NOR}} [[Bente Skari]] <small>(4th title)</small>\n| competition2= Distance\n| competition2men= <small>(not arranged)</small>\n| competition2ladies= <small>(not arranged)</small>\n| competition3= Sprint\n| competition3men= {{flagicon|SWE}} [[Thobias Fredriksson]]\n| competition3ladies= {{flagicon|NOR}} [[Marit Bj\u00f8rgen]]\n| competition4=Nations Cup\n| competition4men= {{flagicon|SWE}} [[Sweden]]\n| competition4ladies= {{flagicon|NOR}} [[Norway]]\n| mixedcompetition1=Nations Cup Overall\n| mixedcompetition1both={{flagicon|NOR}} [[Norway]]\n| menlocations= 19 venues\n| ladieslocations= 19 venues\n| menindividual= 21 events\n| ladiesindividual= 21 events\n| relaymen= 6 events\n| relayladies= 6 events\n| previous=[[2001\u201302 FIS Cross-Country World Cup|2001\u201302]]\n| next=[[2003\u201304 FIS Cross-Country World Cup|2003\u201304]]\n}}\n\nThe '''2002\u201303 FIS Cross-Country World Cup''' was the 22nd official [[FIS Cross-Country World Cup|World Cup]] season in [[cross-country skiing (sport)|cross-country skiing]] for men and ladies. The season began in [[D\u00fcsseldorf]], [[Germany]], on 26 October on 2002 and was concluded in [[Falun]], [[Sweden]], on 23 March 2003. [[Mathias Fredriksson]] of [[Sweden]] won the overall men's cup,<ref>{{cite web|url=http://medias2.fis-ski.com/pdf/2003/CC/2228/2228WC.pdf|title=WORLD CUP STANDING MEN|publisher=[[International Ski Federation]]|accessdate=29 January 2018}}</ref> and [[Bente Skari]] of [[Norway]] won the women's.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://medias1.fis-ski.com/pdf/2003/CC/2227/2227WC.pdf|title=WORLD CUP STANDING WOMEN|publisher=[[International Ski Federation]]|accessdate=29 January 2018}}</ref>\n\n== Calendar ==\n=== Men ===\n{| class=\"wikitable\" style=\"font-size: 90%\"\n|+ C \u2013 Classic / F \u2013 Freestyle\n!width=\"20\"|{{Abbr|WC|World Cup}}\n!width=\"120\"| Date\n!width=\"120\"| Venue\n!width=\"140\"| Discipline\n!width=\"200\"| Winner\n!width=\"200\"| Second\n!width=\"220\"| Third\n!width=\"180\"| Yellow bib\n!width=\"20\"|{{Abbr|Ref.|Reference}}\n|-\n! 1\n| 26 October 2002\n| {{flagicon|GER}} [[D\u00fcsseldorf]] \n| Sprint F\n| {{flagicon|SWE}} [[Peter Larsson (cross-country skier)|Peter Larsson]]\n| {{flagicon|SWE}} [[Thobias Fredriksson]]\n| {{flagicon|NOR}} [[Tor Arne Hetland]]\n| {{flagicon|SWE}} [[Peter Larsson (cross-country skier)|Peter Larsson]]\n| [http://medias2.fis-ski.com/pdf/2003/CC/2038/2038RL.pdf]\n|-\n! 2\n| 23 November 2002\n| {{flagicon|SWE}} [[Kiruna]] \n| 10&nbsp;km F\n| {{flagicon|FRA}} [[Vincent Vittoz]]\n| {{flagicon|ITA}} [[Pietro Piller Cottrer]]\n| {{flagicon|ITA}} [[Fulvio Valbusa]]\n| {{flagicon|NOR}} [[Tor Arne Hetland]]\n| [http://medias3.fis-ski.com/pdf/2003/CC/2147/2147RL.pdf]\n|-\n! 3\n| 30 November 2002\n| {{flagicon|FIN}} [[Rukatunturi|Ruka]]\n| 15&nbsp;km C\n| {{flagicon|RUS}} [[Vasily Rochev (skier, born 1980)|Vasily Rochev]]\n| {{flagicon|CZE}} [[Luk\u00e1\u0161 Bauer]]\n| {{flagicon|GER}} [[Axel Teichmann]]\n| {{flagicon|RUS}} [[Vasily Rochev (skier, born 1980)|Vasily Rochev]]\n| [http://medias1.fis-ski.com/pdf/2003/CC/2485/2485RL.pdf]\n|-\n! 4\n| 7 December 2002\n| {{flagicon|SUI}} [[Davos]]\n| 15&nbsp;km F\n| {{flagicon|SWE}} [[Mathias Fredriksson]]\n| {{flagicon|FRA}} [[Vincent Vittoz]]\n| {{flagicon|ITA}} [[Fulvio Valbusa]]\n| {{flagicon|FRA}} [[Vincent Vittoz]]\n| [http://medias1.fis-ski.com/pdf/2003/CC/2700/2700RL.pdf]\n|-\n! 5\n| 11 December 2002\n| {{flagicon|ITA}} [[Clusone]]\n| Sprint F\n| {{flagicon|NOR}} [[Tor Arne Hetland]]\n| {{flagicon|GER}} [[Ren\u00e9 Sommerfeldt]]\n| {{flagicon|SWE}} [[Anders H\u00f6gberg]]\n| {{flagicon|GER}} [[R